image_analysis.description: A photograph of a mechanical room or utility space. Two large blue industrial blower fans (exhaust fans) are mounted on concrete pads. The foreground fan is labeled 'EF-1'. The background fan is partially obscured by a structural pillar. In the background, there are metal lockers, various pipes, electrical conduits, and a window with bars. A tag hangs from a pipe in the upper left. A rolled-up material or filter is resting on the side of the foreground fan unit.
image_analysis.layout: Industrial interior shot with equipment in the mid-ground and storage/structural elements in the background.

notes: The text 'EF-1' likely stands for Exhaust Fan 1. 'HC-16' is likely a pipe or circuit identifier. The footer 'EFTA00001196' is a Bates-style stamp for document tracking.
